            "body": "I think\n\n> When variable is redeclared, underlying C code will use separate new variable:\n\nwould be a big change and probably not realistic. \n\nA warning would be very reasonable.\n\nOut of interest, how do the main static type analysers treat this? I assume they warn or error?",
